The required new formula for the Remarks column should:
1. Return "Prepaid" when Amount Outstanding is negative.
2. Otherwise, if Over Due Days is blank, return blank.
3. Otherwise, if Over Due Days < 90, return "Call Customer".
4. Otherwise, return "Bad Debts".

Using the existing structured table reference (Table2), the formula becomes:
```
=IF(Table2[[#This Row],[Amount Outstanding]]<0,
    "Prepaid",
    IF(Table2[[#This Row],[Over Due Days]]="",
        "",
        IF(Table2[[#This Row],[Over Due Days]]<90,
            "Call Customer",
            "Bad Debts"
        )
    )
)
```

We will write this formula into every cell of column J (Remarks) for data rows (starting at row 6, since row 5 holds headers). Then we will save the modified workbook to the output directory with the same filename.
